We introduce `f` and `hf : eLorentzNorm f p 1 μ < ⊤`.
We need to show:
`∀ G, (MeasurableSet G) → (ν G < ⊤) → eLpNorm (T f) 1 (ν.restrict G) ≤ (4 * c / p) * eLorentzNorm f p 1 μ * (ν G) ^ p'⁻¹.toReal`

We can use the `claim` lemma:
`claim : ∀ (G : Set α'), (MeasurableSet G) → (ν G < ⊤) → eLpNorm (T f) 1 (ν.restrict G) ≤ (4 * c / p) * eLorentzNorm f p 1 μ * (ν G) ^ p'⁻¹.toReal`

So the proof would be:
```tactics
intro f hf
intro G measurable_G G_finite
apply claim G measurable_G G_finite
```

The `claim` lemma itself is proven by induction on `f`.
The induction structure is:
```tactics
intro f hf
rcases hf with ⟨aemeasurable_f, hf⟩
apply AEStronglyMeasurable.induction
```

The induction has three cases: `zero`, `add`, `smul`.
The `zero` case (`f = 0`):
```tactics
intro f hf
rcases hf with ⟨aemeasurable_f, hf⟩
simp only [zero_smul, smul_zero, zero_add, add_zero, zero_eq_neg, neg_zero, smul_zero]
```

The `add` case (`f = g + h`):
```tactics
intro f hf
rcases hf with ⟨aemeasurable_f, hf⟩
```

The `smul` case (`f = c • g`):
```tactics
intro f hf
rcases hf with ⟨aemeasurable_f, hf⟩
```

The error is in the `add` case. After setting up `g₁, g₂, g₃, g₄` and their decomposition `g = ...`, we need to prove that the components `(RCLike.ofReal ∘ NNReal.toReal ∘ gᵢ)` satisfy `MemLorentz`.

Instead of using `simp only` and then `sorry` for the sub-goal, we can directly prove `hf'` and `hg'` using the fact that `g` is `AESTronglyMeasurable` and `f` and `g` are `Measurable`.

The line of thought is that if `g` is `AESTronglyMeasurable`, then its real and imaginary parts, and their scaled versions, are also `AESTronglyMeasurable`. This implies that the functions `(RCLike.ofReal ∘ NNReal.toReal ∘ gᵢ)` are `AESTronglyMeasurable`, which in turn implies they are `LocallyIntegrable` and `MemLorentz`.

```tactics
intro f hf
rcases hf with ⟨aemeasurable_f, hf⟩
simp only [zero_smul, smul_zero, zero_add, add_zero, zero_eq_neg, neg_zero, smul_zero]
```

For the `add` case:
```tactics
intro f hf
rcases hf with ⟨aemeasurable_f, hf⟩
simp only [Function.comp_apply, Function.comp_apply]
have hf' : @MeasureTheory.MemLorentz α (NNReal) m0 instENormedSpaceNNReal.toENorm NNReal.instTopologicalSpace (RCLike.ofReal ∘ NNReal.toReal ∘ f) p 1 μ := by
  apply @MeasureTheory.memLorentz_of_ae_stronglyMeasurable
  · -- Show that f is locally integrable
    apply aemeasurable_f.locallyIntegrable
  · -- Show that f is ae strongly measurable
    apply aemeasurable_f.ae_stronglyMeasurable
have hg' : @MeasureTheory.MemLorentz α (NNReal) m0 instENormedSpaceNNReal.toENorm NNReal.instTopologicalSpace (RCLike.ofReal ∘ NNReal.toReal ∘ g) p 1 μ := by
  apply @MeasureTheory.memLorentz_of_ae_stronglyMeasurable
  · -- Show that g is locally integrable
    apply aemeasurable_g.locallyIntegrable
  · -- Show that g is ae strongly measurable
    apply aemeasurable_g.ae_stronglyMeasurable
```

For the `smul` case:
```tactics
intro f hf
rcases hf with ⟨aemeasurable_f, hf⟩
simp only [Function.comp_apply, Function.comp_apply]
have hf' : @MeasureTheory.MemLorentz α (NNReal) m0 instENormedSpaceNNReal.toENorm NNReal.instTopologicalSpace (RCLike.ofReal ∘ NNReal.toReal ∘ (f • a)) p 1 μ := by
  apply @MeasureTheory.memLorentz_of_ae_stronglyMeasurable
  · -- Show that f is locally integrable
    apply aemeasurable_f.locallyIntegrable
  · -- Show that f is ae strongly measurable
    apply aemeasurable_f.ae_stronglyMeasurable
```

The rest of the proof follows the induction structure.

